title: Brave explorer climbs into ancient 'satanic' cave – what he finds is truly disturbing
text:
Brave explorer climbs into ancient 'satanic' cave – what he finds is truly disturbing Brave explorer climbs into ancient 'satanic' cave – what he finds is truly disturbing A RENOWNED explorer was left horrified when he discovered gory scenes inside an ancient cave. / Published 22nd February 2017 
Beau Ouimette has gained thousands of followers on his YouTube channel by descending into some of the world’s scariest caves and pits. 
But his latest video – posted on Monday (February 19 – is possibly his most chilling yet. 
The adventurer is seen at the beginning of the video venturing into a dark cave. 
YOUTUBE/AQUACHIGGER TERRIFYING: Beau climbed into a cave and made some horrifying discoveries 
YOUTUBE/AQUACHIGGER STRANGE: Blood was seen splattered on the cave walls “I know there’s going to be a skull in here” Beau Ouimette 
“I’ve heard about a place up here where they have satanic rituals and this might be the very cave that it happens,” he explains. 
Moments later he spots blood splattered across the walls, seeming to confirm his suspicions. 
But the American doesn’t let the haunting sights spook him. 
As he walks further into the pit, he says: “I know there’s going to be a skull in here – maybe just a human tooth.” 
Suddenly, he is stopped in his tracks after spotting “some eyes” looking at him. 
Beau still doesn’t let it deter him and continues his exploration. 
He comes across some sort of animal’s skull, before seeing even more blood all over the wall. 
The YouTube star then sees an opening in the cave, which he speculates is the altar for the sacrifices. 
It’s not known whether these are human or animal sacrifices but soon after, Beau’s cameras zoom in on some strange-looking tracks. 
YOUTUBE/AQUACHIGGER DEAD: He found skulls of various creatures Amazing caves around the world Wednesday, 16th December 2015 These stunning caves are not part of a fairytale, they can be found in some of the world's most remote places in Europe, America and Asia. 1 / 11 Getty Images Antelope Canyon in Arizona was carved out by thousands of years of persistent wind and flash floods, which is why its smooth walls look so smooth and fluid 
“Are these human tracks are some sort of little creature?” he asks. 
“That’s a creature that’s much smaller than us but walks on two legs.” 
As if it wasn’t scary enough, he then spots some sort of writing over a cave wall, before jokingly concluding: “Illumanti CONFIRMED.” 
It’s unclear where the video took place but it has already been viewed more than 20,000 times. Related articles
